til the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]},{"name":"de","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Attainment’."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":25,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When William de Bruario was born in 1190, in Little Saxham, Suffolk, England, his father, Richard de Bruario, was 36 and his mother, Mrs. Richard de Bruario, was 31. He married Mrs. William de Bruario in 1215, in Little Saxham, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died after 1219, in his hometown."},"et":{"1190–after 1219":"1190–pärast 1219","1190–1219":"1190–1219","1195–Female":"1195–Surnud","1216–1293":"1216–1293","1154–1190":"1154–1190","1159–Female":"1159–Surnud","1190":"1190","aft 1190":"pärast 1190","1216":"1216","1215":"1215","1159":"1159","after 1219":"pärast 1219","1179":"1179","1154":"1154","1195":"1195","1293":"1293","1219":"1219","Little Saxham, Suffolk, England":"Little Saxham, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1190–after 1219":"1190–1219 jälkeen","1190–1219":"1190–1219","1195–Female":"1195–Kuollut","1216–1293":"1216–1293","1154–1190":"1154–1190","1159–Female":"1159–Kuollut","1190":"1190","aft 1190":"1190 jälkeen","1216":"1216","1215":"1215","1159":"1159","after 1219":"1219 jälkeen","1179":"1179","1154":"1154","1195":"1195","1293":"1293","1219":"1219","Little Saxham,